==Japanese==
===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[師]] || [[走]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
Literally, 師走 (しわす, ''shiwasu'') means "priests run" (from [[師]], "priest" + [[走]], "run")
: There were traditionally many services for Buddhist priests to attend in the last month of the lunar calendar.

===Noun===
'''師走''' ([[しわす]], ''shiwasu'')

# {{archaic}} the twelfth month of the lunar calendar
# {{poetic}} the month of busy priests; [[December]]

